INSERT INTO "Pages" VALUES (41, 'Nature and Parks', 'http://www.destinationnsw.com.au/smartphoneapps/central-coast/things-to-do/nature-and-parks', 1390517658000, '47', '{"Page":{"Title":"Nature and Parks","Images":[{"Full Size":"http:\/\/www.destinationnsw.com.au\/__data\/assets\/image\/0008\/245780\/1340547.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/www.destinationnsw.com\/__data\/assets\/image\/0008\/245780\/varieties\/thumb.jpg","Alt":"Couple bushwalking through Bouddi National Park","Modified":"2014-01-14 15:07:45"}],"Content":"\r\n<div id=\"content_div_215663\">\r\n<p>The Central Coast offers a host of landscapes to admire and absorb. It\u2019s home to a number of stunning National Parks and forests. Perfect for bushwalking and exploring, there is Brisbane Water National Park, Bouddi National Park, and Strickland State Forest, to name but a few.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>A visit to the area would not be complete without taking one of the many beautiful coastal walks. Walk from MacMasters Beach to Terrigal for the unmissable 5 Lands Coastal Walkway, or for a refreshing experience, take a dip and a walk around Pearl Beach Rock Pool.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Visit Dharug National Park to see UNESCO World Heritage listed Old Great North Road. This is one of Australia\u2019s eleven convict sites, and offers excellent sightseeing and a good walk.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Central Coast\u2019s spectacular coastline is alive with opportunities to experience everything from whale watching to bird watching, paddle-surfing to kayaking, and more.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n"},"Children":[{"Name":"Must Do Links","Url":"http:\/\/www.destinationnsw.com.au\/smartphoneapps\/central-coast\/things-to-do\/nature-and-parks\/must-do-links"},{"Name":"Don\u2019t Miss","Url":"http:\/\/www.destinationnsw.com.au\/smartphoneapps\/central-coast\/things-to-do\/nature-and-parks\/dont-miss"}]}');
