INSERT INTO "Pages" VALUES (47, 'Fashion and Shopping', 'http://www.destinationnsw.com.au/smartphoneapps/central-coast/things-to-do/fashion-and-shopping', 1390517667000, '49', '{"Page":{"Title":"Fashion and Shopping","Images":[{"Full Size":"http:\/\/www.destinationnsw.com.au\/__data\/assets\/image\/0003\/245784\/999176.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/www.destinationnsw.com\/__data\/assets\/image\/0003\/245784\/varieties\/thumb.jpg","Alt":"Close up of sign of Terrigal Surf Shop, Terrigal","Modified":"2014-01-14 15:21:05"}],"Content":"\r\n<div id=\"content_div_215671\">\r\n<p>What better way to spend a lazy weekend morning than browsing the bargains at your favourite market? The Central Coast is home to an array of excellent markets. From monthly markets to seasonal markets, such as the Central Coast Christmas Fair, no matter what your tastes, you are sure to find something to suit you.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Avoca Beachside Markets are well-known throughout the area as the premier artists and musicians market on the Central Coast. Drawing the best creative talent in the region, the markets are the perfect showcase for local artists\u2019 work. Held on the fourth Sunday of every month from 9am-2pm at Heazlett Park, the markets offer live music, a wide selection of international food, excellent stalls, and a backdrop of the beautiful Avoca Beach. Held in the same location on the first Sunday of the month is Avoca Beach Growers Market, 8am-12pm, where you will find a wide range of locally-grown produce.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Meanwhile in Terrigal the Lions Club Car Boot Sale is held on the first Sunday of the month at Terrigal Lagoon Reserve. If you\u2019re looking for something for the kids, check out Terrigal Baby and Kids Market, held on quarterly Sundays at Bridgecoast Stadium.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n"},"Children":[{"Name":"Must Do Links","Url":"http:\/\/www.destinationnsw.com.au\/smartphoneapps\/central-coast\/things-to-do\/fashion-and-shopping\/must-do-links"},{"Name":"Don\u2019t Miss","Url":"http:\/\/www.destinationnsw.com.au\/smartphoneapps\/central-coast\/things-to-do\/fashion-and-shopping\/dont-miss"}]}');
